		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.pathwaytohappiness.com/journal/?p=38</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[If the emotional quality of your life and relationships were solely dependent on how smart you were then you wouldn&#8217;t need a teacher.  But that isn&#8217;t the case.  A book can&#8217;t teach or model for you self acceptance, respect, love, or gratitude.   Being happy in this chaotic world isn&#8217;t based on how smart you are.  [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If the emotional quality of your life and relationships were solely dependent on how smart you were then you wouldn&#8217;t need a teacher.  But that isn&#8217;t the case.  A book can&#8217;t teach or model for you self acceptance, respect, love, or gratitude.   Being happy in this chaotic world isn&#8217;t based on how smart you are.  Even changing beliefs or negative thoughts isn&#8217;t easier because you have a high IQ.</p>
<p>As this free audio explains, mastering your mind and emotions is more like a skill.  Swimming, playing an musical instrument, or flying an airplane are all skills.  If you wanted to learn any of these skills would you get a coach or mentor?    Then if you desired to change your emotional reactions and be happy, wouldn&#8217;t it make sense to get some good guidance as well?  More about this in this free audio.</p>
<p><a title="The choice for a Spiritual Teacher or Guide" href="http://www.pathwaytohappiness.com/podcast/pod21-teacher.mp3" target="_blank"><strong>The Value of a Spiritual Teacher or Guide  Free Audio Podcast (40 min 26 MB)</strong></a></p>
